# SEMVER + Changelog

## Semantic Versioning 2.0.0

- MAJOR: breaking API/behavior changes
- MINOR: new features (backward-compatible) -- triggered by `feat` commits
- PATCH: bug fixes (backward-compatible) -- triggered by `fix` commits

Current version: determined by latest git tag (`git describe --tags`).

## Version Bumping

- `feat` commit -> MINOR bump
- `fix` commit -> PATCH bump
- `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer -> MAJOR bump
- `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs` -> no version bump (included in next release)

## Release Process

1. Merge `develop` into `release/vX.Y.Z` branch
2. Run `make changelog` to regenerate CHANGELOG.md via git-cliff
3. Commit changelog: `chore(release): prepare vX.Y.Z`
4. Merge release branch into `main`
5. Tag: `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "release: vX.Y.Z"`
6. Push tag -- CI runs GoReleaser

## Changelog

- Auto-generated from conventional commits via `git-cliff` (`cliff.toml`)
- Never manually edit `CHANGELOG.md`
- Groups: Features, Bug Fixes, Refactoring, Performance, Testing, Documentation, Miscellaneous

## Binary Version

Injected via ldflags at build time: `-X main.version`, `-X main.commit`, `-X main.date`
